         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Hamburg, ¶  ¶ 7 December ¶  ¶ 1854 ¶ Most ¶  ¶ esteemed ¶  ¶ Professor, ¶  ¶ In consequence of ¶ a lette ¶ r received yesterday from Dr Mue ¶ ller ¶ , ¶ I am ¶ sending you today the treatment of th...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">M54.12.07</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Wilhelm Sonder to Diederich von Schlechtendal</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">MS not seen; text given here extracted from Tkach, Neubauer &amp; Roser (2022), Brief<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">24.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
               </note>Hamburg d.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>7 Dec.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>54<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Geehrtester Herr Professor!<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In folge eines gestern von Dr. Müller erhaltenen Briefes sende ich Ihnen heute die Bearbeitung der zuletzt gesandten Laubmoose. Müller schreib mir, dass von einem Engländer neuseel. und neuholländische Laubmoose beschrieben wurden; damit nun nicht die Müller’schen die Autorität verlieren, sende ich sie lieber jetzt ab u lasse die Algen, die vielleicht noch 3 Wochen Arbeit erfordern, vorläufig zurück. Ich möchte Sie bitten, den Druck möglichst zu beschleunigen und nach Vollendung derselben mir wieder die gewöhnliche Anzahl von Abdrucken zukommen zu lassen.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Meine amtlichen Geschäfte haben mich diesen Herbst mehr wie jemals in Anspruch genommen; erst jetzt kann ich wieder etwas arbeiten. Die letzten Wochen war ich für Senator Binder’s Algen etwas in Arbeit genommen. Binder der kürzlich das Unglück hatte, seine Frau zu verlieren, bedarf sehr der Aufheiterung.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Was das Moosmanuskript anbetrifft, so schrieben Sie mir vor längerer Zeit, Herr C. Müller habe die Moose bearbeitet; nach Hampe’s Brief und nach der Ueberschrift des Manuskriptes hat Hampe deren Theil genommen. Ich glaube wohl, dass Herr C. Müller fähiger zu dieser Arbeit ist als Hampe, dem die Literatur wohl nicht vollständig genug zur Benutzung steht. Die beiden Herren sind alte Freunde, deshalb wird Herr C. Müller, wenn auch ihm vielleicht das Hauptverdienst zu kommt, wohl nichts dagegen haben, dass Hampe’s Name dabeisteht. – Der neuholländische Dr. Müller hat sich sehr über die rasche Bearbeitung der Moose gefreut, er schreibt, dass er emsig nach Laubmoosen suchen werde. Nach seinem am 23. Sept geschriebenen Briefe wollte er nach ca 6 Wochen eine neue Reise in die Alpen unternehmen; sein Bericht über die letzte Reise war in Arbeit. Eine oder zwei Kisten mit Pflanzen sind wieder unterwegs; wegen des Abfalls u der Sämereien werde ich Ihren Wunsch berücksichtigen. Harvey war mehrere Tage bei ihm gewesen, sie haben schöne Algen zusammen gesammelt.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich glaube Ihnen immer noch 5 rT schuldig zu sein. Entschuldigen Sie meine Vergessenheit; aber ich habe immer so viel um die Ohren, dass<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ich wohl manches vergessen muss. Ein 5 Thalerschein liegt bei.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-indent: 0.3333in; "
               xml:lang="de">In der Hoffnung, dass<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Sie meine Bitte um Beschleunigung der Abdrucke erfüllen können, verbleibe ich<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Ihr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>ergebenster<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. Sonder<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Ich habe kürzlich das vor einiger Zeit in der Flora zu Verkauf ausgebotene Herbarium von Leybold acquirirt. Es ist für die Tiroler Flor von grosser Wichtigkeit u enthält noch mancherlei Neues u Interessantes für Deutschlands Flora. Theilweise sind enorme Quantitäten von Doubletten vorhanden. Herr Leybold ist seit einiger Zeit in Hamburg u wohnt in meinem Hause. Er geht nächstens nach Valparaiso, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>wo er ein vortheilhaftes Engagement antritt. Er hat grossen Eifer u wird für die Botanik noch viel leisten.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">d. O.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hamburg,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>7 December<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1854</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Most<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>esteemed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Professor,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">In consequence of</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a lette</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">r received yesterday from Dr Mue</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">ller</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">I am<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">sending you today the treatment of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">mosses<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">last<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">sent</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">. Mue</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">ller wrote me that an Englishman<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">would<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">describe</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>New Zealand and New Holland</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>mosses</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">. Now</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">,</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>so that</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">ue</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">ller</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">’s</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ones do not lose their authority, I prefer to send them<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">off<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">now and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">for the time being<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">leave the algae, which will perhaps require another</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">three</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>weeks of work. I w</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">ould like to ask you to expedite<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">the printing</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as much as possible and after completion to again have</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">the usual number of reprints sent to me.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My official business has taken up more of my time this autumn than ever before.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Only now am I able to do some work again. The last few weeks<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have been somewhat taken in working on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Senator Binder's algae.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Binder who recently had the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>misfortune of losing his wife, is in great need of cheering up.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As far as the moss manuscript is concerned, you wrote me some time ago that Mr. C. Müller had worked on the mosses; according to Hampe's letter and the manuscript's title, Hampe had taken his<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>part. I believe that Mr. C. Müller is more capable of this work than Hampe, for whom the literature is probably not complete enough to use. The two gentlemen are old friends, which is why Mr C. Müller, even if he perhaps deserves most of the credit, will probably not object to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Hampe's name being mentioned. –<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The New<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Holland Dr. Mueller was very pleased about the rapid<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>working up<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the mosses. He writes that he will search diligently for mosses.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">According to his letter written on 23 Sept, he<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">intends</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to undertake a new journey to the Alps after about 6 weeks; his report on the last journey was in progress. One or two boxes</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>plants are on their way again; I will take your</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>wish into consideration on account</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the waste and the seeds. Harvey had been with him<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">several days; they<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">have<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">collected beautiful algae together.</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I think I<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>still<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>owe you 5 Reichstaler.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Excuse my forgetfulness; but I always have so much on my mind that I must have forgotten some things. A 5<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Taler<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>note is enclosed.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the hope that you can fulfil my request to expedite the printing, I remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>most<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>devoted</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. Sonder</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have recently acquired Leybold's herbarium, which was offered for sale in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Flora<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>some time ago. It is of great importance for the Tyrolean flora and contains many new and interesting things for Germany's flora. In part there are enormous quantities of duplicates. Mr. Leybold has been in Hamburg for some time and lives in my house. He will be going to Valparaiso in the near future, where he will take up an advantageous engagement. He has great zeal and will do much for botany.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">The above named.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
